description: A simple JavaScript library to help you quickly identify unseemly images; all in the client's browser. NSFWJS isn't perfect, but it's pretty accurate... and it's getting more accurate all the time.
title: NSFW JS
keywords: NSFW detection, TensorflowJS, NSFWJS, NSFWJS Demo, JavaScript, NPM, Node Module
introduction: Drag and drop an image to check for false positives, camera, and blur protection.
targetPeople: Users who want to check images for false positives and protect against camera and blur issues

faqs.question: What can I check with this tool?
faqs.answer: You can check for false positives, camera issues, and blur protection in images.

faqs.question: Is there a free trial available?
faqs.answer: The availability of a free trial is not specified.
